1268	\subsection{Toward the iter-055+ comparison theorem (informal scoping)}
1269	
1270	Mathlib has $\mathtt{cechComplexFunctor}$ (\texttt{Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/SheafCohomology/Cech.lean}) but \emph{no} comparison theorem to derived-functor cohomology. The substantive iter-055+ obligation is to construct, for any sheaf $F$ on $C.\mathtt{left}$ and cover $\mathcal U$ with $[\IsCechAcyclicCover\,F\,\mathcal U]$ (\emph{or} a slightly weaker hypothesis), a natural $\LinearEquiv$
1271	\[
1272	  \mathrm{compIso}_n \,:\, \cechCohomology\,C\,F\,\mathcal U\,n \;\equiv_k\; \HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,\big(\bigsqcup_i \mathcal U_i\big), \qquad \forall n.
1273	\]
1274	The standard mathematical decomposition is the \emph{Cartan-Leray spectral sequence} (Stacks 03OU; Wikipedia ``Čech-to-derived functor spectral sequence''):
1275	\[
1276	  E_2^{p,q} \;=\; \check H^p\big(\mathcal U,\, \underline{H^q}(F)\big) \;\Longrightarrow\; H^{p+q}\big(\bigsqcup\mathcal U,\, F\big),
1277	\]
1278	which under the acyclicity hypothesis $\check H^q(\mathcal U_{i_0..i_p}, F) = 0$ for $q > 0$ collapses on the $E_2$ page to give $\check H^n \cong H^n$. Mathlib does not have the spectral-sequence machinery in the required form; the project-local construction is therefore expected via the dual chain-level Mayer-Vietoris sheaf-resolution route (Stacks 01EO):
1279	\begin{enumerate}
1280	  \item Construct the augmented sheaf-level complex $\mathcal{F}_{\bullet} \,:\, n \mapsto \bigoplus_{i_0 < \cdots < i_n} (j_{i_0\cap\cdots\cap i_n})_! ((\mathtt{presheafToSheaf}).\mathrm{obj}((\mathtt{yoneda} \circ \free\,k).\mathrm{obj}\,\mathcal U_{i_0\cap\cdots\cap i_n}))$ with augmentation to $(\mathtt{presheafToSheaf}).\mathrm{obj}((\mathtt{yoneda}\circ\free\,k).\mathrm{obj}\,(\bigsqcup\mathcal U))$ (sheafified Mayer-Vietoris resolution of the free sheaf on $\bigsqcup\mathcal U$). Show this complex is exact in positive degrees under acyclicity (the substantive computational step; alternating-face complex is exact, equivalently the local-section complex on each $\mathcal U_{i_0..i_p}$ is the Koszul complex of localisations exact under unit-ideal hypothesis).
1281	  \item Apply $\Hom(-, F)$ degree-wise, picking up $\Hom(\mathcal{F}_n, F) \cong \prod_{i_0,\ldots,i_n} F(\mathcal U_{i_0\cap\cdots\cap i_n}) = (\cechCochain)_n$ on the LHS, and $\Hom\big((\mathtt{presheafToSheaf}).\mathrm{obj}\,(\mathtt{yoneda}\circ\free\,k).\mathrm{obj}\,(\bigsqcup\mathcal U),\, F\big) = \HModulePrime\,k\,F\,0\,(\bigsqcup\mathcal U)$ on the RHS at degree 0.
1282	  \item Pass to cohomology and chain to $\Ext^n$ via the augmentation; under acyclicity the augmentation is a quasi-iso, and the induced map on $\Ext^n$ gives the comparison.
1283	\end{enumerate}
